<tr><td valign=top width=100% height=100% style='background: url(intr/background2.png) #f2f2f2; padding-top: 30px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 30px;'>
<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td><nobr><a href='tutorials/macplus1988'><img width=9 height=20 style='margin-right: 10px' border=0 alt='Go back' src='intr/2captions/goback.png'><img border=0 alt='Mac Plus tour' hspace=0 src='intr/2captions/macplustour.png'></a></td><td valign=top height=20><img width=19 height=20 align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3toprise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x'><img border=0 alt='Introduction' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3captions/introduction.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=20 style='background: url(intr/3topleftfill.png) top repeat-x'><img width=20 height=20 hspace=0 src='intr/3topleft.png'></td><td valign=top><img align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3topleftrise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>

<p>
<table class=reg cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 border=0>

<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/001.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Welcome to Your Apple&reg; Tour of the Macintosh&reg;</b>
</p><p>
If you&rsquo;ve used this tour before, you may skip to the Main Menu by clicking the mouse button.
</p><p>
&copy; 1987, 1988 Apple Computer, Inc.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/002.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/003.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Right now, thousands of people are using the Apple Macintosh computer to get things
done. You can, too.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/004.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Using a Macintosh requires three essential skills: pointing, clicking, and dragging.
Once you&rsquo;ve mastered them, you&rsquo;ll be ready to get to work.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/005.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Skill #1: POINTING.</b> Move the mouse on the table. You&rsquo;ll see that a pointer
moves on the screen.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/006.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
That&rsquo;s right. Try picking up the mouse and putting it down somewhere else on the table.
Notice that the pointer on the screen doesn&rsquo;t move.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/007.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Remember this when you run out of space for your mouse: You can always pick up the mouse
and put it down in a better position.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/008.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Practice pointing. Move the pointer so it touches each of the numbers in order.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/009.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You have just learned skill #1: POINTING. By moving the mouse, you can point at anything
on the screen. Point at this arrow to go on.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/010.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Skill #2: CLICKING.</b> Pressing and releasing the mouse button is called clicking. Try
it now.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/011.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
That&rsquo;s right. When you point to an object on the screen and press the mouse button, you&rsquo;re
clicking that object. Clicking makes something happen. Click this arrow to go on.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/012.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Practice clicking. Click each of the closed windows. Click the forward arrow to go on.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/013.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/014.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/015.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/016.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>

</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/017.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You have just learned skill #2: CLICKING. Clicking is one way of telling your Macintosh what
to do. From now on, click the forward arrow to go on.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/018.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Skill #3: DRAGGING.</b> One way of getting things done with the Macintosh is by moving
objects around on the screen. This is called dragging. You drag by holding the mouse button
down as you move the mouse.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/019.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Practice dragging. Move the letters onto the theater marquee by following these steps:
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100% class=list><tr><td width=16><img width=16 height=9 src='intr/liststart.png'></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Point at the letter you want to move (starting with &ldquo;D&rdquo;).
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Press the mouse button, and hold it down as you move the letter onto the theater marquee.
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width=16 background='intr/listfill.png' valign=top><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=16 height=15 src='intr/listbullet.png'></td><td width=100%><table width=100% class=list cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td valign=top width=5 valign=middle><img style='margin-top: 0.5em' width=5 height=15 src='intr/listbulletfill.png'></td><td class=content width=100%>Release the mouse button.
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><img width=16 height=8 src='intr/listend.png'></td></tr></table></p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/020.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Good. You have just learned to DRAG. You&rsquo;ll use dragging in several different ways when
you work with the Macintosh.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=512 height=342 src='pics/tutorials/macplus1988/introduction/021.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Now you know the three essential Macintosh skills: pointing, clicking and dragging. The rest
of this tour will show you how to use them in your work.
</p></td></tr>


</table></p>

</td><td height=50 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'><img width=12 height=1 src='intr/3rightfill.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td height=30><img width=20 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/3bottomleft.png'></td><td height=30 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3bottomfill.png)'></td><td height=30><img width=30 height=30 hspace=0 src='intr/3bottomclosed.png'></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr>

